==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Galactose
<hw>Ga*lac"tose</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A white, crystalline sugar, <chform>C6H12O6</chform>, isomeric with
dextrose, obtained by the decomposition of milk sugar, and also from
certain gums. When oxidized it forms mucic acid. Called also
<altname>lactose</altname> (though it is not lactose proper).</def><--
lactose is a dimeric form of galactose, converted to galactose by acid
or enzymatic activity (beta-galactosidase) -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Galage</ent>⟦br⟧
